This paper is about embeddings in Clinical Natural Language Processing, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper discusses various embeddings models and their applications in the clinical domain, which makes it highly likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses evaluation methods and challenges in clinical embeddings, which could also make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses medical codes, which could make it relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses possible future directions for research in clinical embeddings, which could make it relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
